token_lists.title: BREACH cyclus
token_lists.description:
The Breach NFT cyclus offers a seven-folded perspective on the live AV performance, diving into chaotic systems and creating a manifestation of events of protests and riots across the globe. The works create an ever-looping build up and release of tension, anger and energy in a new form of pitch black electronics and dense polyrhythmic structures. Utilising electromagnetic recordings of communication devices and found footage of uproars Breach establishes intense loops on the verge of breaking into chaos. 

“BREACH sloganeers: Your anger is a gift. BREACH unleashes: what was kept pent up, creeping slow like glacier ice, but advancing surely as the scorching lava that entombed Herculaneaum. Leaving behind the spiked blast of unloading, BREACH does not represent – fashions disruptive events: compositions of chaos in flux. BREACH breathes the frantic fumes and pulsates with the moving noises of electromagnetic rebels in the streets: this, the density of today. For BREACH is manifest.” [words by Sven Schlijper-Karssenberg]

token_lists.title: Lightseeker Crew
token_lists.description:
In the solar systems on the outer rim of the Virgo galaxy, light has started fading from the suns.

The unexplained phenomenon has the population on the surrounding planets are in uproar and civilizations are bursting in the seams, chaos looming.

Ancient prophecies speak of this event as "The return to darkness"; predicting death, destruction and the end of all things. Only a “Lightbringer” can stop the catastrophe and bring order back to the galaxy.

The planetary alliance has assembled an unlikely crew tasked with finding the mythic “Lightbringer” and stop the looming catastrophe.

Kinacia: Crewleader
Pinto: Pilot
Lex: Priestess
Micah: Lightseeker
Radunia: Ship mechanic

token_lists.title: Vessel Crew Challenge - AAC Crew Loki
token_lists.description:
Atlas Adventurer Catalogue Crew Loki sailed in on the island's shore though the mist, another low visability morning. Fishing vessels had been disappearing off the colony south coast and it the air smelled afoul of magic. Atilith had a nose for these things and always trusted her gut. Adorned in a peacock colored fur she stepped off the boat and tried to drink in  the scene in silence. For a moment she saw what happened, then the stupid whirr of Coua's headset broke her attention. She'd begged him to keep his distance, but it seemed he'd locked in on the same spot she had. "All my metrics point to a ritual here, though I can't quite analyze what." he grumbled, meeting her gaze through the visor.

"I might have discerned but I lost it, bring the oracles out, we should be close enough to pinpoint what happened." With that three figures started to made their way down the gangplank to the muddy shore.

"No no no not you. There's no trouble here Risighti, keep your distance I can't afford another ARZ for Coua if you decide to toss a stray punch his way again". The muscle in the tiger mask grumbled and lurched back on to the boat. Diversity is great for achieving different perspectives, but bitter rival gangs proved to be a bit too much for Atilith to handle most days. As the oracles made their way down to where she and Coua stood, they parted and let the two work magic they couldn't begin to understand.

Dixon and Jenkins, perhaps the two least magically endowed names imaginable knelt on the muddy shore, atuning to one another. She leaned in, rarely one to listen in but the two seemed eager today.  Jenkins opened his mouth, but only to calm the chittering monster on his shoulder. Their eyes suddenly lit up a glowing azure, Dixon's altered voice making the air resonate with the tone.

"What is it we seek?"

Jenkins spoke next, the two exchanging dialogue in that strange alien wavelength "The source of the ritual"

"No, we know the source. We seek the truth they sought"

"It lives in darkness. It cannot be tamed"

"Then shine a light"

Jenkins' eyes pierced the hazy morning fog as they shone brighter suddenly, "Ugly son of a bitch"

"Don't speak of elder gods so"

"So you knew? Why test me?"

"A whetstone to your blade"

"My blade cannot slay a god, nor yours"

"Not yet, but we know more today than we did before"

With that their eyes faded, both collapsing forward with both arms into the muck. Atilith hated this dumb ritual, but that night the two would likely catalog an encyclopedia of knowledge about whatever was causing this chaos. She didn't understand it but it worked. Sometimes that was enough. She gave a whistle to call for Risighti, who stepped down and slung either man over each shoulder, hauling them back to the boat. He paused a moment and hocked a grotesque spitball at Coua's feet before dragging the two oracles up onto the deck. Coua groaned, "Aren't you going to reprimand him?"

"He's just mad you couldn't carry one, not get on deck." she bellowed.

A motley crew was a very polite way of describing them. Deep down she couldn't stand the lot.
